{
  "doc_id": "60048",
  "text": "Another route to couple parareal algorithm with control strategy is given in the paper [CITATION_1] where we decompose the control problem over [0, T ] on a series of independent control problems over each intervals [T n , T n+1 ] with intermediate initial conditions at time T n and intermediate target values at time T n+1 that have to be designed following an iterative procedure. The method has been proposed and implemented first for the control of Schrödinger equation in [CITATION_2] with a very nice implementation of a harder problem in [CITATION_3] and proves also to be very successful. This frame with an hyperbolic equation where the adjoint equation is the same as the primal problem makes the design and the analysis of the iterative method to define iteratively the intermediate initial condition and intermediate target values more easy than in the parabolic case. This case is under investigation.",
